1. System Overview
The Crypto Watcher is an automated cryptocurrency price monitoring system built using Make.com as the automation backbone. The system fetches live crypto data from the CoinGecko public API, applies filtering logic to detect significant price movements and trending coins, delivers real-time alerts via Telegram and Slack, logs all data to Google Sheets, and displays a live dashboard via a Lovable-generated frontend UI.
 
The system is triggered via a webhook that can be called on a schedule by cron-job.org or manually via the Run Monitor button in the Lovable dashboard. Once triggered, the scenario branches into two independent paths — one for monitoring tracked coin prices and one for detecting globally trending coins.
Core components:
•   	Make.com — handles all automation, data retrieval, filtering and notifications
•   	CoinGecko API — provides free real-time cryptocurrency market data with no API key required
•   	Google Sheets — serves as the data store and live bridge between Make.com and the frontend
•   	Lovable — generates and hosts the responsive frontend dashboard
•   	cron-job.org — external free scheduler that triggers the Make.com webhook on a set interval
•   	Telegram Bot — receives price alert notifications
•   	Slack — receives trending coin notifications
 
 
 
