Data returned per coin:
•   	current_price — current price in USD
•   	price_change_percentage_24h — percentage change over last 24 hours
•   	market_cap — total market capitalisation
•   	total_volume — 24-hour trading volume
•   	last_updated — ISO timestamp of last data update
•   	image — URL of the coin logo
4.2 Iterator
An Iterator module loops through the array of coins returned by the HTTP module. Without the Iterator, Make.com would treat all three coins as a single bundle. The Iterator splits them so every downstream module processes each coin individually — one bundle per coin, three total runs through the rest of Branch 1.
Configuration: Array field is set to Data[] from the HTTP module output.
4.3 Sleep Module
A Tools → Sleep module is placed between the Iterator and the second HTTP module, set to 2000 milliseconds (2 seconds). This delay prevents hitting CoinGecko's free tier rate limit when making individual coin detail calls in rapid succession for each coin in the loop.
4.4 HTTP Module — Fetch Coin Metadata
A second HTTP module calls the CoinGecko /coins/{id} endpoint for each individual coin to retrieve metadata not available from the markets endpoint. The coin ID is dynamically populated from the Iterator using the {{id}} variable.
GET https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/coins/{{id}}
Additional data returned:
•   	links.homepage[0] — official website URL
•   	description.en — coin description text
•   	Additional metadata fields
4.5 Google Sheets — Log All Coins
Before applying any alert filter, two Google Sheets modules log every coin's data regardless of whether its price change meets the threshold. This is a critical design decision — the dashboard must always display all tracked coins, not just the ones that triggered alerts.
Two modules run sequentially for each coin:
•   	First module writes to the Latest tab — this is what the Lovable dashboard reads
•   	Second module writes to the History tab — this maintains a permanent audit log
Alert Type is set to the static text 'Price Alert' for all rows on this branch.
4.6 Filter — Price Change Threshold
A Filter module checks whether the coin's 24-hour price change percentage exceeds the alert threshold. Only coins that pass this filter continue to the Telegram notification. Coins that do not pass are silently stopped — they have already been logged to Google Sheets in the previous step.
Filter conditions:
price_change_percentage_24h Greater than 5
OR
price_change_percentage_24h Less than -5
This catches both upward spikes and significant drops. The threshold can be adjusted by editing the filter condition values.
4.7 Telegram Bot — Price Alert Notification
For coins that pass the filter, a Telegram Bot module sends an alert message to a configured chat ID. The Telegram bot is created via BotFather and connected to Make.com via the bot token.
