6.4 Publishing the CSV URL for Lovable
To connect the Google Sheet to the Lovable dashboard:
•   	Open the Google Sheet and click File → Share → Publish to web
•   	In the first dropdown select the Latest tab specifically (not Entire Document)
•   	In the second dropdown select Comma-separated values (.csv)
•   	Click Publish and copy the generated URL
•   	Paste this URL into the Lovable project as the data source
The published URL contains a gid parameter that uniquely identifies the Latest tab, ensuring Lovable always reads only that tab and never the History tab.
7. Lovable Frontend Dashboard
7.1 Overview
A responsive frontend dashboard was built using Lovable at lovable.dev and deployed as a public web application. The dashboard reads data from the Google Sheets Latest tab via the published CSV URL and automatically refreshes every 60 seconds to display current data.
Live URL: coin-hearth-monitor.lovable.app

Figure 2: Lovable dashboard showing Monitored Coins, Trending Coins, Price Alerts panel and 24h Change chart


7.2 Dashboard Features
•   	Header — displays total market cap of monitored coins and last updated timestamp
•   	Price Alerts panel — highlights coins exceeding the threshold with a live count and adjustable slider from 1% to 20%. Solana showing -5.43% is highlighted as it exceeds the 5% threshold
•   	24h Price Change chart — bar chart with green bars for gains and red bars for losses, toggleable between 24h Change % and Volume (B) views
•   	Monitored Coins section — displays cards for all rows where Alert Type = Price Alert, showing price, 24h change %, market cap, volume and last updated time. Solana's card is highlighted in red as it triggered an alert
•   	Trending Coins section — displays cards for all rows where Alert Type = Trending Alert, showing coin name, symbol, market cap rank and last updated time
•   	Run Monitor button — top right button that sends a POST request to the Make.com webhook URL to trigger an immediate scenario run
•   	Auto refresh — fetches fresh CSV data from Google Sheets every 60 seconds automatically
•   	Fully responsive — works on both mobile and desktop screens
7.3 How the Dashboard Connects to Make.com
The connection between Lovable and Make.com works through two mechanisms:
Google Sheets CSV (data display): Make.com writes coin data to Google Sheets after every run. Lovable reads the published CSV URL every 60 seconds and renders the data on screen. This means the dashboard always reflects the output of the last Make.com scenario run.
Webhook button (manual trigger): The Run Monitor button in the dashboard sends a POST request directly to the Make.com webhook URL. This allows triggering the full scenario on demand without waiting for the cron-job.org schedule.
 
