8. How to Maintain the System
8.1 Changing Tracked Coins
•   	Open Make.com and edit the first HTTP module on Branch 1
•   	Update the ids query parameter with new CoinGecko coin IDs
•   	Use lowercase IDs as they appear on CoinGecko (e.g. bitcoin, ethereum, solana)
•   	Keep the total to 5 coins or fewer on the free CoinGecko tier to avoid rate limit errors
•   	Save and run once to confirm the new coins appear in Google Sheets and on the dashboard
8.2 Changing the Alert Threshold
•   	Open Make.com and click the Filter module on Branch 1
•   	Update the condition values from 5 and -5 to your desired percentage
•   	Save the filter — the change takes effect on the next scenario run
•   	The threshold slider on the Lovable dashboard is a frontend-only UI control — it does not change the Make.com filter
 
8.3 Adding a New Notification Channel
•   	Add a new module after the Filter on Branch 1 (Email, SMS via Twilio, etc)
•   	Connect your account credentials through Make.com's connection manager
•   	Map the same coin data fields to the message template using the variable picker
•   	Save and trigger the webhook once to test the new channel
8.4 Extending to More Coins
•   	Add more coin IDs to the ids parameter in HTTP module on Branch 1
•   	Increase the Sleep module delay to 300secs or more if rate limit errors occur
•   	Consider upgrading to a paid CoinGecko API key for higher rate limits if tracking more than 10 coins
 
