10. Known Limitations
•   	CoinGecko free tier rate limit: The public API allows approximately 10-30 calls per minute. The Sleep module mitigates this but tracking more than 5 coins simultaneously may still cause occasional rate limit errors. A paid API key resolves this.
•   	Make.com free plan operations: The free plan provides 1,000 operations per month. Running every 30 minutes uses approximately 720 operations per month for 3 tracked coins. Increasing coin count or run frequency may exceed this limit.
•   	Google Sheets CSV cache delay: The published CSV URL has a cache delay of up to 5 minutes. This means the Lovable dashboard may display data that is slightly behind the most recent Make.com run.
•   	Threshold slider is frontend only: The alert threshold slider on the Lovable dashboard controls only the visual highlight on the dashboard. It does not update the Make.com filter condition. To change the actual alert threshold, the filter in Make.com must be edited directly.
 
